1 13. "Radio system" means a private network for voice
2 communications;
3 14. “Real-time communications network” means private licensed
4 radio frequencies, channels, or talk-groups, on either a wire or
5 wireless communication network, that allows for real-time voice or
6 data transmissions between a public safety answering point, specific
7 school safety team members, school district safety teams, and first
8 responders;
9 15. "Revolving fund" means the School Access for Emergency
10 Response Revolving Fund created in Section 6 of this act;
11 16. "Safety team" means personnel who have a role in crisis
